🖥️ 28. Azure Compute Services & Virtual Machines (VMs)
☁️ Azure Compute Services

👉 Services that provide processing power to run applications.

✔ Examples:

Virtual Machines
App Services
Containers
Functions
🖥️ Virtual Machines (VMs)

👉 A virtual computer in the cloud.

✔ You can:

install OS
run apps
control everything

💡 Meaning:

“A computer you rent in Azure”

📈 29. VM Scale Sets (VMSS)

👉 Automatically creates and manages multiple identical VMs.

✔ Used for:

handling high traffic
auto-scaling apps

💡 Meaning:

“More users → more VMs automatically”

⚖️ 30. Availability Sets & Proximity Groups
🏗️ Availability Sets

👉 Keeps VMs in different hardware groups to avoid failure.

✔ If one server fails, others still run.

📍 Proximity Groups

👉 Keeps resources physically close in same data center region.

✔ Reduces latency (faster communication)

🚀 31. App Services, Containers, Azure Virtual Desktop
🌐 App Services

👉 Platform to host web apps easily
✔ No server management needed

📦 Containers

👉 Lightweight package with app + dependencies
✔ Runs same everywhere

🖥️ Azure Virtual Desktop

👉 Cloud-based Windows desktop
✔ Access your PC from anywhere

⚡ 32. Azure Functions

👉 Serverless computing service

✔ Runs code only when triggered
✔ No server management
✔ Pay only when used

💡 Meaning:

“Run small pieces of code on demand”

🌐 33. Azure Networking Services

👉 Services that connect and secure cloud resources.

✔ Includes:

Virtual Network (VNet)
Load Balancer
Firewall
VPN

💡 Meaning:

“Networking system for cloud apps”

🔗 34. Network Peering, DNS, VPN Gateway
🔗 VNet Peering

👉 Connects two virtual networks directly.

🌍 Azure DNS

👉 Converts domain names → IP addresses
✔ Example: google.com → IP

🔐 VPN Gateway

👉 Secure connection between:

on-premises network ↔ Azure cloud
🔐 35. Public & Private Endpoints
🌍 Public Endpoint

👉 Accessible from internet

🔒 Private Endpoint

👉 Accessible only inside private network

💡 Meaning:

Public = open access
Private = secure internal access

